				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">BTW, speaking of the pet ignoring you while you're getting attacked...
<br />

<br />
I've had this happen to me often recently, both with my beastlord and with my necro.  I have discovered that when this happens, it's always been because my pet was aggro'd on another mob that had warped away or something, and my pet *thought* it was still chasing it or something, when it was really just walking along next to me... even if I'm in melee at the moment.
<br />

<br />
The trick to resolve this is to hit the /pet back off key once.  This clears the pet's aggro list, which means it suddenly wakes up and says "Woah, master's being attacked!  Charge!"<br />_________________<br />&lt;br&gt;<div align=center><img src="http://www.digikitten.com/playhousev2/files/Tipop/notherkrag.jpg" width="500" height="200" border="0" usemap="#nothermap"><map name="nothermap"><area alt="Fury of Faith" coords="31,157,152,187" href="http://members.telocity.com/~Tipop2000/fury"><area alt="Tipop's Homepage" coords="186,157,321,187"  href="http://members.telocity.com/~Tipop2000/"><area alt="Kraggan's Magelo Profile" coords="342,157,465,186" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=120506"></map></div></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
